articles.title: XRobotics’ countertop robots are cooking up 25,000 pizzas a month
articles.description: XRobotics recently raised a $2.5 million seed round to help it produce more of its countertop pizza robots.

articles.description: Anthropic was experimenting with an AI-generated blog. TechCrunch profiled it. Then, Anthropic shut it down.

articles.title: Qualcomm to acquire semiconductor firm Alphawave Semi for $2.4B
articles.description: Qualcomm has acquired Alphawave Semi, a U.K.-based semiconductor company focused on high-speed data center connectivity, for around $2.4 billion.
articles.author: Kyle Wiggers

articles.title: OpenAI updates ChatGPT’s voice mode with more natural-sounding speech
articles.description: ChatGPT's natural-sounding voice mode just got a big update, including more natural-sounding synthetic voice options.
articles.author: Kyle Wiggers

articles.title: Meta reportedly in talks to invest billions of dollars in Scale AI
articles.description: Meta is discussing a multi-billion dollar investment in Scale AI, according to Bloomberg. In fact, the deal value could reportedly exceed $10 billion, making it the largest external AI investment for the Facebook parent company and one of the largest funding events ever for a private company.
articles.author: Anthony Ha

articles.title: Lawyers could face ‘severe’ penalties for fake AI-generated citations, UK court warns
articles.description:
he High Court of England and Wales says lawyers need to take stronger steps to prevent the misuse of artificial intelligence in their work.

In a ruling tying together two recent cases, Judge Victoria Sharp wrote that generative AI tools like ChatGPT “are not capable of conducting reliable legal research."
articles.author: Anthony Ha

articles.title: Trump administration takes aim at Biden and Obama cybersecurity rules
articles.description: In a White House fact sheet, the administration claims that Biden’s Executive Order 14144 — signed days before the end of his presidency — was an attempt “to sneak problematic and distracting issues into cybersecurity policy.”
articles.author: Anthony Ha

articles.title: Why investing in growth-stage AI startups is getting riskier and more complicated
articles.description: AI startups are reaching growth stage much faster. That's exciting, but also risky, because investors might pour millions into a company only to watch it be unseated in a few months.

articles.title: Humans provide necessary ‘checks and balances’ for AI, says Lattice CEO
articles.description: In an interview with TechCrunch after her SXSW appearance, Franklin said Lattice has built an AI HR agent that gives proactive insights and assists employees in one-on-one meetings. The company also has a platform where Lattice clients can create their own custom agents for their businesses. Franklin was adamant that humans must have oversight of any AI technology implemented by a company.
